{
  "texts": [
    "By tracking and optimizing energy and resource consumption, organizations can identify areas for improvement and reduce their data center's carbon footprint, fostering overall sustainability in data center operations.",
    "RefactoringRefactoring practices are addressed to existing software and infrastructure that are not optimized for low carbon emission.",
    "Following the dedicated pillar in Fig. 1, these practices include software refactoring and application optimization, cloud optimization, code/architecture redesign, and environment management.",
    "Software refactoring and applications optimizationSoftware refactoring involves restructuring code to enhance quality, maintainability, and efficiency without altering functionality.",
    "Sustainable software refactoring extends this practice by integrating green software engineering principles [55][56][57][58], focusing on identifying and addressing energy-intensive or resource-heavy code patterns."
  ]
}